---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Copilot Code Review">
  <h1>GitHub Copilot Code Review</h1>
  <p>
    Every pull request in this repo — including the AI-drafted one that kicks off the live demo —
    gets an automatic first pass from Copilot Code Review before a human ever looks at it.
  </p>
  <p>It reads the diff and leaves inline comments for things a linter usually misses:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>A third-party GitHub Action pinned to a tag instead of a commit SHA</li>
    <li>A workflow requesting broader permissions than the job needs</li>
    <li>A missing <code>integrity</code>/<code>crossorigin</code> attribute on a third-party script</li>
    <li>A form handler with no input validation</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    None of these are "vulnerabilities" a dependency scanner would catch — they're judgment
    calls about code quality and defensive coding. That's the point: Copilot Code Review is the
    reviewer that reads intent, not just signatures.
  </p>
</Layout>
